[48;2;42;45;68m [38;2;154;165;206m↳[39m ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────                [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    weak_sigreg_loss — the math                                                                                                                           [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    Input                                                                                                                                                 [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    ·  z  ∈ ℝ^{N×C} — pooled context embeddings, N tokens, C channels                                                                                     [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    ·  target_std  — desired per-channel standard deviation (default 1.0)                                                                                 [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    ·  sketch_dim  k — projection dimension for covariance penalty (default 64)                                                                           [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    ·  eps  — numerical stabilizer (default 1e-4)                                                                                                         [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    Step 1 — Center                                                                                                                                       [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    z = z − mean(z, dim=0)          # subtract per-channel mean                                                                                           [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    Step 2 — Variance hinge (full C dimensions)                                                                                                           [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m   For each channel j ∈ {1…C}:                                                                                                                            [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    std_j = √( var(z[:,j]) + ε )        [var is population variance: sum/N]                                                                               [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m   Then:                                                                                                                                                  [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    var_loss = (1/C) · Σⱼ ReLU(target_std − std_j)                                                                                                        [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m   Behavior: If channel j has std ≥ target_std → contributes 0. If collapsed → contributes up to target_std. Gradient exists even at exact zero           [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m   (through  √(var+ε)  and the  −std_j  term inside ReLU).                                                                                                [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    Step 3 — Random orthogonal sketch (only if C > k)                                                                                                     [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    if C > k:                                                                                                                                             [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m        sketch = randn(C, k)           # Gaussian random matrix                                                                                           [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m        sketch = QR(sketch).Q          # orthogonalize via QR                                                                                             [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m        z_proj = z @ sketch            # ∈ ℝ^{N×k}                                                                                                        [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    else:                                                                                                                                                 [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m        z_proj = z                                                                                                                                        [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m   This projects the C-dimensional embeddings onto a random k-dimensional subspace. The QR decomposition ensures the projection is uniformly              [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m   random among orthonormal k-frames — unbiased in expectation.                                                                                           [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    Step 4 — Off-diagonal covariance penalty (sketched)                                                                                                   [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m   On the k-dimensional projection:                                                                                                                       [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    cov = (z_projᵀ · z_proj) / (n−1 + ε)    # k×k, unbiased denominator                                                                                   [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    cov_off = cov − diag(diag(cov))          # zero out diagonal                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    cov_loss = (1/k) · Σᵢⱼ (cov_off)²       # mean squared off-diagonal                                                                                   [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m   Behavior: Penalizes correlation between projected dimensions. If all k projected axes are uncorrelated → cov_off ≈ 0 → loss ≈ 0. If they're            [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m   perfectly correlated (e.g. all z_proj columns are the same up to scaling) → large off-diagonals → large loss.                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    Step 5 — Combine                                                                                                                                      [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    loss = var_loss + cov_loss                                                                                                                            [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m   Both terms contribute additively with equal weight (1:1).                                                                                              [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    Step 6 — Batch-size gradient scaling                                                                                                                  [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    effective_n = 256                                                                                                                                     [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    if n > effective_n:                                                                                                                                   [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m        scale = n / effective_n                                                                                                                           [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m        loss = loss × scale  −  detach(loss) × (scale − 1)                                                                                                [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m   The detach trick:  loss.detach()  has no autograd history, so the subtraction removes the value inflation while the  loss × scale  term passes         [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    the scaled gradient through. Net effect: the loss number logged doesn't grow with batch size, but the gradient does.                                  [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    Intuition                                                                                                                                             [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m   Two complementary pressures:                                                                                                                           [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    1. Variance hinge pushes each channel's std toward ≥ target_std — prevents dead channels, works on ALL C dimensions directly.                         [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    2. Covariance penalty pushes off-diagonal correlations toward zero in a random k-dimensional view — discourages the embedding from collapsing         [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m        to a low-dimensional subspace without paying O(C²) for the full covariance matrix.                                                                [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m   The sketch makes the covariance term O(C·k) instead of O(C²). The variance term is already O(C). The random projection rotates every call so           [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m   no particular correlation pattern can be "learned around."                                                                                             [49m
