[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  ```markdown                                                                                                                                             [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  # `sajepa` — Scale-Aware JEPA for Continuous Physical Fields                                                                                            [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  [![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)                                             [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  [![Python 3.9+](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.9+-blue.svg)](https://www.python.org/)                                                            [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  [![PyTorch 2.0+](https://img.shields.io/badge/PyTorch-2.0+-ee4c2c.svg)](https://pytorch.org/)                                                           [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  `sajepa` is a non-generative, self-supervised framework factory designed to extract **pixel-registered latent coordinates** from continuous physical    [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  fields (e.g., magnetohydrodynamic turbulence, fluid continuums, and multi-wavelength astronomical data).                                                [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  By coupling **Constrained Diffusion Decomposition (CDD)** with a **Joint-Embedding Predictive Architecture (JEPA)**, the network treats spatial masking [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m   as a sequence of scale-specific structural interventions. This forces the predictor to learn invariant physical transport operators natively from      [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  scratch without representation collapse or pixel reconstruction artifacts.                                                                              [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  ---                                                                                                                                                     [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  ## [7G [6G🏛️[8G Core Architecture                                                                                                                                 [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  Unlike traditional vision world models that utilize discrete, object-centric bounding boxes or fixed-scale token masking, `sajepa` operates under a     [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  scale-space paradigm optimized for continuums where clear boundaries do not exist:                                                                      [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  * **No Object Slots:** Replaces discrete entity tracking with continuous scale hierarchies.                                                             [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  * **Scale-Informed Masking:** Synthesizes masking footprints directly from the local diffusion scales of the field.                                     [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  * **Glass-Box Constraints:** Leverages CDD to process scalar inputs as explicit, scale-separated components while retaining absolute pixel              [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  registration.                                                                                                                                           [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  ---                                                                                                                                                     [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
