[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  ```                                                                                                                                                     [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  The model predictor outputs explicit coordinate-wise variance maps ($\sigma^2$), pointing directly to regions where the model experiences structural    [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  uncertainty (e.g., turbulent vortex boundaries, supersonic shock lines) versus regions where the localized physics are trivial.                         [49m
