[48;2;42;45;68m [38;2;154;165;206m↳[39msajepa — Scale-Aware JEPA for Continuous Physical Fields                                                                                                [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  sajepa is a non-generative, self-supervised framework factory designed to extract pixel-registered latent coordinates from continuous physical fields   [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  (e.g., magnetohydrodynamic turbulence, fluid continuums, and multi-wavelength astronomical data).                                                       [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  By coupling Constrained Diffusion Decomposition (CDD) with a Joint-Embedding Predictive Architecture (JEPA), the network treats spatial masking as a    [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  sequence of scale-specific structural interventions. This forces the predictor to learn invariant physical transport operators natively from scratch    [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  without representation collapse or pixel reconstruction artifacts.                                                                                      [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  [4G [3G🏛️[5G Core Architecture                                                                                                                                    [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  Unlike traditional vision world models that utilize discrete, object-centric bounding boxes or fixed-scale token masking, sajepa operates under a       [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  scale-space paradigm optimized for continuums where clear boundaries do not exist:                                                                      [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
