[48;2;42;45;68m  [4G [3G🛠️[5G Auto-Batch OOM Safeguards                                                                                                                            [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  To accommodate high-resolution spatial data, sajepa includes a native memory abstraction layer. If the GPU encounters a CUDA Out-Of-Memory (OOM) error, [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m   the training engine dynamically catches the error, halves the current batch size, and scales the gradient accumulation steps proportionally to         [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  preserve the targeted effective batch size.                                                                                                             [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  YAML                                                                                                                                                    [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m                                                                                                                                                          [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  # configs/mhd_turbulence.yaml                                                                                                                           [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m  training:                                                                                                                                               [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    batch_size: 4                                                                                                                                         [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    target_batch_size: 32                                                                                                                                 [49m
[48;2;42;45;68m    auto_scale_batch_size: "power_of_two"  # Catches OOM and scales: 4 → 2 → 1                                                                            [49m
